description: >-
  Michigan-specific employee restrictive covenant agreement built for MCL
  § 445.774a(1): confidentiality and trade-secret protection backstopped by the
  Michigan Uniform Trade Secrets Act (MCL §§ 445.1901–445.1910), customer and
  employee non-solicitation, an optional non-compete gated on a reasonable
  competitive business interest and sized reasonably as to duration, geographic
  area, and line of business (St. Clair Medical, P.C. v. Borgiel; Mid Mich. Med.
  Billing Serv., Inc. v. Williams), a consideration recital keyed to Michigan's
  continued-employment-in-an-at-will-setting rule (QIS, Inc. v. Industrial
  Quality Control, Inc.), a general-knowledge-and-skill carve-out (Follmer,
  Rudzewicz & Co., P.C. v. Kosco), a paired governing-law and forum-selection
  provision (Stryker Corp. v. Ridgeway; Barshaw v. Allegheny Performance
  Plastics, LLC), physician proof-of-diversion scrutiny (Isidore Steiner, DPM,
  PC v. Bonanni), and statutory blue-pencil reformation that the drafting does
  not rely on (MCL § 445.774a(1) empowers a court to limit an unreasonable
  covenant and enforce it as limited, but the power is discretionary). Drafted as
  a starting point for licensed counsel review.
