    display_label: Employee Non-Solicitation Duration
    default: 24 months
    section: Employee Non-Solicitation
    rationale_source: editorial
    default_value_rationale: >-
      Michigan sets no statutory cap on duration; reasonableness turns on the state's general
      restrictive-covenant reasonableness analysis rather than a fixed number. 24 months matches the
      modal employee non-solicit term observed in benchmarked, publicly-filed employee agreements;
      12 months is the common lighter alternative for this least-scrutinized covenant in the family,
      which counsel should size to the employer's actual protectable interest.
